# Baseline Whitelist — known-good source IPs.
#
# One IPv4 address per line. Lines starting with '#' are comments.
# Matching source IPs are forced to "Baseline (Safe)" regardless of
# rule trips or RF prediction. Threat-intel matches still win — a
# whitelist entry will not protect an IP that also appears on the
# threat-intel feed.
#
# Typical entries: your gateway, DNS server, the dashboard host, any
# device that legitimately bursts traffic during speed tests / OS
# updates and trips bandwidth-spike rules.
#
# Copy this file to baseline.txt and edit. The runtime loads
# baseline.txt only — this .example file is ignored.

# 192.168.1.1     # home gateway / router
# 192.168.1.10    # internal DNS resolver
# 10.0.0.5        # dashboard host
